caption.text:
Hi guys, time for another review.  It's for the BW-100, Electronic  Contact Cleaner. I've seen this up for Try's numerous times, bt I never tried it. Well, that's changed & I'm really happy I did. It has special trick, it'll spray upside down, which is really convenient! Don't you hate that when you're trying to write & your pen goes out or there's an awkward placement of the  blueray & when finally are able to reach it & it wont work at that angle? That won't happen w BW-100 Contact Cleaner, has 360 rotation technology & it can spray reversely, which I don't really understand. However, the straw isnt needed ,you can spray just regular in those areas too. 
Directions: 
A) Shake the can very well. 
B) Attach the long red straw for pinpointing small hard to get to places. 
C) Hold the can 8 in away from surface & spray  directly on the electronic device or circuit board 
D) Wait & the solvents disappear 
Some features of the product: 
Non-flammable
Environmentally friendly /Zero harm to ozone
Residue free
Quick dry
Safe on metal, plastic, rubber 
My thoughts:
My mom's mifi device was acting up, so I thought I'd try this new spray. Well, to noth of our surprise, it worked! A quick spray & voila, all done. That is the only electronic that was having problems, bt I cleaned my other electronics & now they're all nice & clean. I enjoyed using this & will recommend it, if I know someone who needs this type of product. Very similar to WD-40. 
Note:
I purchased this item at a reduced price for my honest opinion/review. I'd like to thank 0.8l & BEX BW-100, for making this review possible!  My mom's mifi device was acting pretty squirrelly ,so
